#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code Maximal Rectangle problem ko histogram problem me convert karke solve karta hai.

1. Har row ko histogram ki tarah treat karte hain.
   - Agar matrix[i][j] = '1' ho, to his[j] ko +1 kar dete hain
   - Agar '0' ho, to his[j] = 0 kar dete hain
2. Is tarah har row ke liye continuous 1's ki height ban jaati hai.
3. Ab har updated histogram par largestRectangleArea() call karte hain.
4. largestRectangleArea me har bar ke liye:
   - previous smaller index
   - next smaller index
   nikaal kar width find karte hain.
5. Area = height * width
6. Har row ke histogram se max area nikaal ke overall maxArea update kar dete hain.

Main idea:
2D matrix ko directly solve nahi kar rahe,
balki har row tak ke 1's ko histogram bana ke
“Largest Rectangle in Histogram” wala logic apply kar rahe hain.

Time Complexity: O(rows * cols)
Space Complexity: O(cols)

#Code:

import java.util.Deque;
import java.util.ArrayDeque;

public class Solution{
  public int maximalRectangle(char[][] matrix)
  {
      //You can code here
      int row = matrix.length;
      if(row == 0) return 0; //for to prevent arrayBound error
      int col = matrix[0].length;
      int maxArea = 0;
      int[] his = new int[col];
      for(int i=0; i<row; i++){
        for(int j=0; j<col; j++){
          if(matrix[i][j] == '0'){
            his[j] = 0;
          }else{
            his[j]++;
          }
        }
        int currArea = largestRectangleArea(his);
        maxArea = Math.max(maxArea, currArea);
      }
      return maxArea;    
  }
  public int[] previousSmaller(int[] heights){
        int n = heights.length;
        ArrayDeque<Integer> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();
        int[] ans = new int[n];

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            while(!stack.isEmpty() && heights[stack.peek()] >= heights[i]){
                stack.pop();
            }

            if(stack.isEmpty()){
                ans[i] = -1;
            }
            else{
                ans[i] = stack.peek();
            }
            stack.push(i);
        }
        return ans;
    }
    public int[] nextSmaller(int[] heights){
        int n = heights.length;
        ArrayDeque<Integer> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();
        int[] ans = new int[n];

        for(int i=n-1; i>=0; i--){
            while(!stack.isEmpty() && heights[stack.peek()] >= heights[i]){
                stack.pop();
            }

            if(stack.isEmpty()){
                ans[i] = n;
            }
            else{
                ans[i] = stack.peek();
            }
            stack.push(i);
        }
        return ans;
    }

    public int largestRectangleArea(int[] heights) {
        int n = heights.length;
        int[] ps = previousSmaller(heights);
        int[] ns = nextSmaller(heights);
        int maxVal = 0;

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            int curr = (ns[i] - ps[i] - 1) * heights[i];
            maxVal = Math.max(maxVal, curr);
        }
        return maxVal;

    }
}
